  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to evaluate the safety and efficacy of Rifaximin in the treatment
      of cirrhotic gastroesophageal variceal bleeding.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Gastroesophageal variceal bleeding is the most common and life-threatening condition in
      patients with portal hypertension, which are susceptibility to bacterial infection.

      However, the prophylaxis use of antibiotics remained uncertain and lack of high level
      evidences.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
